a pit bull terrier unhappy with the smell coming from shipping crates full of oriental statues led u.s. customs officials to up to $1.8 billion worth of heroin at o'hare international airport, authorities said
it was the largest inland port seizure of heroin in united states history,'' u.s. attorney anton valukas said monday after authorities announced the arrest of six people on drug charges
spike, a pit bull terrier trained to locate drugs by the u.s. customs service, sniffed suspiciously at the seven shipping crates destined for new york from bangkok, thailand, on british airways on feb. 5, said his handler, customs officer jeff gabel
gabel alerted superiors, and the statues were uncrated and put through x-ray machines and other scans. inside, authorities found 165 pounds of high-quality asian heroin worth up to $1.8 billion
agents opened the crates, cracked the statues and removed most of the heroin. then they repaired the figures, put them back into the crates and followed the shipping orders that said the crates should be sent to a house in norridge, near o'hare, said barry elden of the u.s. attorney's office in chicago
agents watched as four people rented a truck and drove the statues to new york, elden said
six suspects were arrested in new york on sunday and charged with conspiracy to possess with intent to distribute heroin, elden said
the suspects, who were held without bond, were identified as prasit maneerat of bangkok; chang zhu-yu and kaw ting-ti, both of ocean, n.y.; chen woi-kong of new york; eng chuck jor of yonkers, n.y.; and tang chi-lap of brooklyn, n.y
the latest seizure and recent record seizures of cocaine and hashish indicate that chicago has become a major shipment point for drugs, valukas said
congress plans to hold hearings regarding allegations that haiti's top military officers have been smuggling cocaine into the united states, according to a published report
the san francisco examiner reported in today's editions that alfred cumming, a legislative aide to sen. bob graham, d-fla., said the hearings are scheduled to start in mid-march
cumming said the hearings, to be headed by sen. joseph biden, d-del., or sen. john kerry, d-mass, will be in response to concern ``about the allegations of haitian cocaine trafficking.''
the hearings will investigate reports that haiti, with the participation of top military officials, has become a major shipment and refueling point for drugs and guns since february 1986, when former haitian president jean-claude duvalier was replaced by a military junta
a federal source, familiar with a current probe by the u.s. attorney's office in miami, said that haiti was ``probably another example of a military that is up to its earlobes in drug operations,'' the newspaper said
for the last year, a federal grand jury has been focusing on police chief col. jean-claude paul, whose ranch and airstrip 90 miles from port-au-prince has been used by cocaine smugglers, said u.s. drug enforcement agency investigators
the examiner reported that a congressional source who has been briefed on the federal probe said an indictment against paul and several relatives and associates is imminent
