shevardnadze arrived in prague this morning to a welcome from foreign minister bohuslav chnoupek, then went to the foreign ministry in the cernin palace to inform colleagues of the latest superpower talks on arms reduction and afghanistan
ctk quoted foreign ministry spokesman dusan rovensky as saying shevardnadze briefed warsaw pact colleagues ``in a profound and all round manner'' about his talks with shultz
the foreign ministry reported two hours after the session began that the warsaw pact ministers had ended their talks
shultz and sheverardnadze concluded two days of talks in moscow earlier today, when the secretary of state departed for brussels to brief nato foreign ministers. the superpower ministers said their negotiating session moved the superpowers closer to a strategic arms agreement and a spring summit in moscow
besides chnoupek, foreign ministers attending today's session in prague included romania's ioan totu and bulgaria's peter mladenov
