the cheapest round-trip fares on american airlines and delta air lines, often used by vacationers, will increase $10 and similar fares offered by united airlines also will go up, company officials said
the increases are in so-called maxsaver fares used on or after march 2. if tickets are purchased before that date, but travel is ater, additional cost will be included in the faon that day or lre price, the airlines said monday
maxsaver tickets, only available on round-trip travel, are not refundable and must be purchased within 24 hours of making reservations
the price hike follows a fare increase announced by major airlines last week. american and delta, dallas-fort worth airport's dominant carriers, as well as braniff inc. and other major airlines said they would raise unrestricted coach fares by $5 each way on most routes
